   "source": [
    "# 03 — Benchmarking Local LLMs\n",
    "\n",
    "Compare models on latency and throughput across prompt lengths.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Concepts:** Controlled benchmarking, prompt scaling, model comparison, measurement methodology\n",
    "\n",
    "Tests all 4 models at short/medium/long prompts.\n",
    "\n",
    "Requires Ollama running with all 4 benchmark models pulled.\n",
    "\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Definition\n",
    "\n",
    "LLM benchmarking measures **latency** (time to generate, in seconds) and **throughput** (tokens per second) across models and input sizes. These metrics answer practical questions:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Which model should I use for a real-time chatbot? (needs low latency)\n",
    "- Which model should I use for batch document summarization? (needs high throughput)\n",
    "- How does prompt length affect performance? (scaling behavior)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook uses `BenchmarkRunner` from `src/benchmarking.py` to run controlled tests across 4 models at 3 prompt lengths."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Motivation\n",
    "\n",
    "Model quality is subjective. Performance metrics are objective. Benchmarking answers:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Is the 4B model worth 2x the latency over the 2B model?\n",
    "- Does Granite 4.1:3b offer a sweet spot?\n",
    "- At what prompt length does each model become impractical for real-time use?\n",
    "\n",
    "Without benchmarking, deployment decisions are guesses. With it, you have data for cost-latency-quality tradeoffs."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Theory: Measurement Methodology\n",
    "\n",
    "**What we measure:**\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Latency (seconds)**: Wall-clock time from request start to full response. Measured via `measure_inference_time()` on `OllamaClient`.\n",
    "2. **Tokens**: Number of tokens generated (`eval_count` from Ollama response).\n",
    "3. **Throughput (tok/s)**: `tokens / latency` — how fast the model output\n",
    "\n",
    "**Controlled variables (held constant):**\n",
    "- `temperature=0.0` — deterministic, reproducible output\n",
    "- System prompt format — same task framing across models\n",
    "- Prompt length categories: short (50 tok), medium (200 tok), long (500 tok)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Sources of variance (acknowledged):**\n",
    "- CPU/GPU thermal throttling\n",
    "- Ollama's model caching (cold vs warm start)\n",
    "- System load from other processes\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "BenchmarkRunner.run_all()\n",
    "  └── for each model (4) x prompt length (3) x 1 run each\n",
    "       ├── generate() with timing wrapper\n",
    "       └── collect {latency_s, tokens, tok_per_sec}\n",
    "  └── return dict[model][length_label] -> metrics\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Real-World Examples\n",
    "\n",
    "| Use Case | Latency Budget | Model Choice |\n",
    "|---|---|---|\n",
    "| Real-time chatbot | < 2s per response | qwen3.5:2b |\n",
    "| Batch document processing | Minutes per document | qwen3.5:4b |\n",
    "| Translation pipeline | Depends on doc length | translategemma:4b |\n",
    "| Semantic search | < 500ms per query | qwen3-embedding:4b |\n",
    "\n",
    "Benchmark results directly inform these deployment decisions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Visual Explanation\n",
    "\n",
    "**Benchmark pipeline:**\n",
    "\n",
    "```\n",
    "┌─────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────┐\n",
    "│ 4 Models     │    │ 3 Prompt Lengths  │    │ Measurement       │\n",
    "│             │    │                  │    │                  │\n",
    "│ qwen3.5:2b  │    │ short (50 tok)   │    │ latency_s        │\n",
    "│ qwen3.5:4b  │───→│ medium (200 tok) │───→│ tokens           │\n",
    "│ granite4.1  │    │ long (500 tok)   │    │ tok_per_sec      │\n",
    "│ nemotron-3  │    │                  │    │                  │\n",
    "└─────────────┘    └──────────────────┘    └──────────────────┘\n",
    "                          │\n",
    "                          ▼\n",
    "                  ┌──────────────────┐\n",
    "                  │ BenchmarkRunner  │\n",
    "                  │ .run_all()      │\n",
    "                  │ → dict          │\n",
    "                  └──────────────────┘\n",
    "                          │\n",
    "                          ▼\n",
    "                  ┌──────────────────┐\n",
    "                  │ BenchmarkVis.    │\n",
    "                  │ .generate_all() │\n",
    "                  │ → PNG files     │\n",
    "                  └──────────────────┘\n",
    "```"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Code Walkthrough"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 1. Import and inspect benchmark configuration\n",
    "# MODELS: list of 4 model names to test\n",
    "# PROMPT_LENGTHS: dict of label -> prompt text\n",
    "from src.benchmarking import BenchmarkRunner, PROMPT_LENGTHS, MODELS\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Models: {MODELS}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Prompt lengths: {list(PROMPT_LENGTHS.keys())}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 2. Run the full benchmark\n",
    "# This calls generate() for each model x length combination\n",
    # \"Caution: will take 1-5 minutes depending on hardware\"\n",
    "runner = BenchmarkRunner()\n",
    "data = runner.run_all()\n",
    "runner.close()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Print results table\n",
    "for model, lengths in data.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n{model}:\")\n",
    "    for label, m in lengths.items():\n",
    "        tps = m['tokens'] / m['latency_s'] if m['latency_s'] > 0 else 0\n",
    "        print(f\"  {label:8s}  {m['latency_s']:6.2f}s  {m['tokens']:5d} tokens  {tps:5.1f} tok/s\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 3. Quick analysis — identify fastest and best throughput\n",
    "fastest = min(data, key=lambda m: data[m][\"short\"][\"latency_s\"])\n",
    "print(f\"Fastest on short prompt: {fastest}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "best_throughput = max(data, key=lambda m: data[m][\"long\"][\"tokens\"] / max(data[m][\"long\"][\"latency_s\"], 0.001))\n",
    "print(f\"Best throughput on long prompt: {best_throughput}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 4. Generate visualization figures\n",
    "# Creates 4 chart types: latency bar, latency line, throughput, radar\n",
    "# Saves to outputs/figures/\n",
    "from src.visualization import BenchmarkVisualizer\n",
    "\n",
    "vis = BenchmarkVisualizer()\n",
    "paths = vis.generate_all(data)\n",
    "for name, path in paths.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"{name}: {path}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 5. Display generated charts inline\n",
    "from IPython.display import Image, display\n",
    "for name, path in paths.items():\n",
    "    print(f\"--- {name} ---\")\n",
    "    display(Image(filename=path))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Best Practices\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Set `temperature=0.0`** — ensures deterministic, reproducible results across runs\n",
    "2. **Warm up the model first** — first inference call includes model loading; discard or note it\n",
    "3. **Measure end-to-end latency**, not just model inference — network and serialization matter\n",
    "4. **Always report both latency and throughput** — one metric alone is misleading (low latency doesn't mean high throughput)\n",
    "5. **Test at multiple prompt lengths** — scaling behavior reveals inflection points\n",
    "6. **Run multiple iterations** — single runs have high variance; report mean/std"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Common Mistakes\n",
    "\n",
    "| Mistake | Fix |\n",
    "|---|---|\n",
    "| Only measuring latency (ignoring throughput) | Report both: latency for user-facing, throughput for batch |\n",
    "| Testing only shortest prompt | Scale matters — test at production-like input sizes |\n",
    "| Not accounting for cold starts | First inference after model load is slower; run warm-up first |\n",
    "| Single-run measurements | Run 3-5 iterations and report mean ± std |\n",
    "| Using default temperature (≠ 0) | Non-deterministic output adds noise to timing comparison |\n",
    "| Forgetting to close clients | File descriptor leaks affect subsequent measurements |"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "- Larger models (qwen3.5:4b) have higher latency but may produce better quality\n",
    "- Smaller models (qwen3.5:2b) better for real-time applications\n",
    "- Granite 4.1:3b balances size and performance\n",
    "- Throughput (tok/s) matters more than raw latency for batch processing\n",
    "- Prompt length scales latency roughly linearly within context window"
   ]
  }
